CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 20, 1941, pg. 9, reads: "Newlyweds of the Week - Among one of the season's loveliest brides was Miss Ella Mae Fullam, who was married to Thurston Mosely. The ceremony was performed Monday, Sept. 15 at the Monumental Baptist church. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Groom Thurston Mosely wearing tuxedo and light colored bow tie, and bride Ella Mae Fullam Mosely wearing long sleeved gown with embroidery around sweetheart neckline, wide waistband, and holding prayer book with ribbons and ferns, standing in interior with checkered floor
